article.description: Liz Sherwood  finished with 16 points as Vanderbilt defeated Arkansas 64-59 Thursday night.
article.headline: No. 20 Vanderbilt pulls away to beat Arkansas
article.linkText: No. 20 Vanderbilt pulls away to beat Arkansas
article.story:
NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Liz Sherwood, the nation's leader in
field-goal shooting, was 7-for-9 and finished with 16 points as Vanderbilt (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today, No. 22 AP) defeated Arkansas 64-59 Thursday night.

Vanderbilt (17-7, 6-4 Southeastern Conference) took its biggest
lead of the first half when Cherish Stringfield hit a 3-pointer
with 2:29 remaining in the period, giving the Commodores a 35-28
advantage.

Arkansas (13-10, 5-5), which beat Vanderbilt 52-51 at home on
Jan. 8, came back from a 46-35 deficit 5 minutes into the second
half. Dominique Washington's 3-pointer at the 8:16 mark capped the
Razorbacks' 16-6 run to pull within one.

Sherwood followed with a basket and Dee Davis hit a free throw
to push Vanderbilt's lead to 55-51.

Melissa Hobbs made a basket to cut Arkansas' deficit to 55-53,
but never got any closer as Vanderbilt was 7-for-12 on free throws
the rest of the way.

Carla Thomas finished with 11 points and Davis had 10 for the
Commodores.

Leslie Howard led Arkansas with nine points, and Hobbs had 11
rebounds.
